This paper discusses the integration of privacy enhancing techniques into blockchains, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of sidechains, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Garlic Routing and Onion Routing, which are techniques related to network security and privacy (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for improving privacy in blockchains, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
